'''Kymi''' was a rural municipality in [[Finland]], located in [[Kymenlaakso]] on the coast, about 100&nbsp;km east of Helsinki. Kymi is now part of [[Kotka]]. Its population in 1939 was 21,241 and in 1944 20,924.

